130	208	681	681	he	5	2,"The happiest hour of the day both for the old man and his dog was when the man returned from his work in the field . Having finished his frugal supper of rice and vegetables , he would take what he had saved from the meal out to the little veranda that ran round the cottage . Sure enough , Shiro was waiting for his master and the evening tit - bit . Then the old man said "
